{"type":"app","meta":{"headers":{"x-nextjs-stale-time":"300","x-nextjs-prerender":"1","x-next-cache-tags":"_N_T_/layout,_N_T_/problems/layout,_N_T_/problems/[slug]/layout,_N_T_/problems/[slug]/[lang]/layout,_N_T_/problems/[slug]/[lang]/page,_N_T_/problems/find-the-safest-path-in-a-grid/cpp"},"segmentPaths":["/_tree","/_full","/problems/$d$slug/$d$lang/__PAGE__","/problems/$d$slug/$d$lang","/problems/$d$slug","/problems","/_index","/_head"]},"html":"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charSet=\"utf-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\"/><link rel=\"preload\" href=\"/_next/static/media/797e433ab948586e-s.p.0r6juujl39pe6.woff2\" as=\"font\" crossorigin=\"\" type=\"font/woff2\"/><link rel=\"preload\" href=\"/_next/static/media/caa3a2e1cccd8315-s.p.0wgildi0cnwt9.woff2\" as=\"font\" crossorigin=\"\" type=\"font/woff2\"/><link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/_next/static/chunks/340fxer6uczx7.css\" data-precedence=\"next\"/><link rel=\"preload\" as=\"script\" fetchPriority=\"low\" href=\"/_next/static/chunks/05kafvajig4wu.js\"/><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/2o5-igl1ik8oj.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/1uejzok0tpgy1.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/3ujjz4ap-oopx.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/turbopack-3om3j4o09b7fr.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/0a2gmow1_jiq0.js\" async=\"\"></script><meta name=\"next-size-adjust\" content=\"\"/><title>Find the Safest Path in a Grid C++ Solution | AlgoForge</title><meta name=\"description\" content=\"C++ solution for Find the Safest Path in a Grid (LeetCode #2812). Time O(n^2), space O(n^2).\"/><meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"Find the Safest Path in a Grid cpp,Find the Safest Path in a Grid C++,cpp leetcode\"/><link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/find-the-safest-path-in-a-grid/cpp\"/><meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Find the Safest Path in a Grid C++ Solution | AlgoForge\"/><meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"C++ solution for Find the Safest Path in a Grid (LeetCode #2812). Time O(n^2), space O(n^2).\"/><meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/find-the-safest-path-in-a-grid/cpp\"/><meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"AlgoForge\"/><meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://algoforge.dev/og-default.png\"/><meta property=\"og:image:width\" content=\"1200\"/><meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"630\"/><meta property=\"og:image:alt\" content=\"Find the Safest Path in a Grid C++ Solution | AlgoForge\"/><meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\"/><meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\"/><meta name=\"twitter:title\" content=\"Find the Safest Path in a Grid C++ Solution | AlgoForge\"/><meta name=\"twitter:description\" content=\"C++ solution for Find the Safest Path in a Grid (LeetCode #2812). Time O(n^2), space O(n^2).\"/><meta name=\"twitter:image\" content=\"https://algoforge.dev/og-default.png\"/><link rel=\"icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico?favicon.2vob68tjqpejf.ico\" sizes=\"256x256\" type=\"image/x-icon\"/><link rel=\"icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\"/><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/0cz1d0mv5g_q7.js\" noModule=\"\"></script></head><body class=\"geist_deef94d5-module__Sms4YG__variable geist_mono_1bf8cbf6-module__FlyLvG__variable antialiased\"><div hidden=\"\"><!--$--><!--/$--></div><script>((a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h)=>{let i=document.documentElement,j=[\"light\",\"dark\"];function k(b){var c;(Array.isArray(a)?a:[a]).forEach(a=>{let c=\"class\"===a,d=c&&f?e.map(a=>f[a]||a):e;c?(i.classList.remove(...d),i.classList.add(f&&f[b]?f[b]:b)):i.setAttribute(a,b)}),c=b,h&&j.includes(c)&&(i.style.colorScheme=c)}if(d)k(d);else try{let a=localStorage.getItem(b)||c,d=g&&\"system\"===a?window.matchMedia(\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\").matches?\"dark\":\"light\":a;k(d)}catch(a){}})(\"class\",\"theme\",\"system\",null,[\"light\",\"dark\"],null,true,true)</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"AlgoForge\",\"url\":\"https://algoforge.dev\",\"description\":\"AlgoForge is a free, SEO-first coding interview platform with pattern-based learning paths, curated collections (Blind 75, Grind 169), multi-language solutions, and original explanations.\"}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"WebSite\",\"name\":\"AlgoForge\",\"url\":\"https://algoforge.dev\",\"description\":\"AlgoForge is a free, SEO-first coding interview platform with pattern-based learning paths, curated collections (Blind 75, Grind 169), multi-language solutions, and original explanations.\",\"potentialAction\":{\"@type\":\"SearchAction\",\"target\":{\"@type\":\"EntryPoint\",\"urlTemplate\":\"https://algoforge.dev/search?q={search_term_string}\"},\"query-input\":\"required name=search_term_string\"}}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"SoftwareApplication\",\"name\":\"AlgoForge\",\"applicationCategory\":\"EducationalApplication\",\"operatingSystem\":\"Web\",\"offers\":{\"@type\":\"Offer\",\"price\":\"0\",\"priceCurrency\":\"USD\"},\"description\":\"AlgoForge is a free, SEO-first coding interview platform with pattern-based learning paths, curated collections (Blind 75, Grind 169), multi-language solutions, and original explanations.\"}</script><header class=\"sticky top-0 z-50 border-b border-border/80 bg-background/85 backdrop-blur-md\"><div class=\"container-af flex h-14 items-center justify-between gap-4\"><div class=\"flex items-center gap-6\"><a class=\"flex items-center gap-2 font-bold tracking-tight\" href=\"/\"><span class=\"inline-flex h-7 w-7 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-primary text-primary-foreground text-xs font-black\">AF</span><span class=\"hidden sm:inline\">AlgoForge</span></a><nav class=\"hidden lg:flex items-center gap-1\" aria-label=\"Main\"><a class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-muted transition-colors\" href=\"/problems\">Problems</a><a class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-muted transition-colors\" href=\"/topics\">Topics</a><a class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-muted transition-colors\" href=\"/patterns\">Patterns</a><a class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-muted transition-colors\" href=\"/roadmaps\">Roadmaps</a><a class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-muted transition-colors\" href=\"/blind-75\">Blind 75</a><a class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-muted transition-colors\" href=\"/companies\">Companies</a><a class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground hover:bg-muted transition-colors\" href=\"/blog\">Blog</a></nav></div><div class=\"flex items-center gap-1\"><a class=\"hidden sm:inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card px-3 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:border-primary/40 transition-colors\" href=\"/search\"><span>Search…</span><kbd class=\"rounded border border-border bg-muted px-1.5 text-[10px] font-mono\">/</kbd></a><a class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground\" href=\"/dashboard\">Progress</a><button class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50 hover:bg-muted text-foreground h-9 w-9\" aria-label=\"Toggle theme\"></button></div></div></header><main id=\"main\" class=\"min-h-[70vh]\"><div class=\"container-af py-10\"><nav aria-label=\"Breadcrumb\" class=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\"><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://algoforge.dev/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Problems\",\"item\":\"https://algoforge.dev/problems\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Find the Safest Path in a Grid\",\"item\":\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/find-the-safest-path-in-a-grid\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":4,\"name\":\"C++\",\"item\":\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/find-the-safest-path-in-a-grid/cpp\"}]}</script><ol class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5\"><li class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\"><a class=\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\" href=\"/\">Home</a></li><li class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"text-border\">/</span><a class=\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\" href=\"/problems\">Problems</a></li><li class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"text-border\">/</span><a class=\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\" href=\"/problems/find-the-safest-path-in-a-grid\">Find the Safest Path in a Grid</a></li><li class=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"text-border\">/</span><span class=\"text-foreground font-medium\" aria-current=\"page\">C++</span></li></ol></nav><div class=\"mt-4 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\"><span class=\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-medium/15 text-medium\">Medium</span></div><h1 class=\"mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight\">Find the Safest Path in a Grid<!-- --> — <!-- -->C++</h1><p class=\"mt-2 text-muted-foreground\"><a class=\"text-primary hover:underline\" href=\"/problems/find-the-safest-path-in-a-grid\">Full explanation</a> · <!-- -->Time <!-- -->O(n^2)<!-- --> · Space <!-- -->O(n^2)</p><div class=\"mt-8\"><div class=\"rounded-xl border border-border overflow-hidden bg-code-bg text-slate-100\"><div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-2 border-b border-white/10 bg-black/30 px-2 py-1.5\"><div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-1\" role=\"tablist\" aria-label=\"Language\"><button role=\"tab\" aria-selected=\"true\" class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-medium transition-colors bg-white/15 text-white\">C++</button><button role=\"tab\" aria-selected=\"false\" class=\"rounded-md px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-medium transition-colors text-slate-400 hover:text-white hover:bg-white/5\">Python</button></div><button class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50 px-3 text-sm text-slate-300 hover:text-white hover:bg-white/10 h-8\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Copy code\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-copy h-3.5 w-3.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><rect width=\"14\" height=\"14\" x=\"8\" y=\"8\" rx=\"2\" ry=\"2\"></rect><path d=\"M4 16c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V4c0-1.1.9-2 2-2h10c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2\"></path></svg>Copy</button></div><pre class=\"overflow-x-auto p-4 text-[13px] leading-relaxed font-mono max-h-[32rem]\"><code>// Time:  O(n^2)\n// Space: O(n^2)\n\n// bfs, bucket sort, union find\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    int maximumSafenessFactor(vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt;&amp; grid) {\n        static const vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; DIRECTIONS = {{1, 0}, {0, 1}, {-1, 0}, {0, -1}};\n        const auto&amp; bfs = [&amp;]() {\n            vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt; dist(size(grid), vector&lt;int&gt;(size(grid[0]), -1));\n            vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; q;\n            for (int r = 0; r &lt; size(grid); ++r) {\n                for (int c = 0; c &lt; size(grid[0]); ++c) {\n                    if (grid[r][c]) {\n                        dist[r][c] = 0;\n                        q.emplace_back(r, c);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            int d = 0;\n            for (int d = 0; !empty(q); ++d) {\n                vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; new_q;\n                for (const auto&amp; [r, c] : q) {\n                    for (const auto&amp; [dr, dc] : DIRECTIONS) {\n                        const int nr = r + dr, nc = c + dc;\n                        if (!(0 &lt;= nr &amp;&amp; nr &lt; size(dist) &amp;&amp; 0 &lt;= nc &amp;&amp; nc &lt; size(dist[0]) &amp;&amp; dist[nr][nc] == -1)) {\n                            continue;\n                        }\n                        dist[nr][nc] = d + 1;\n                        new_q.emplace_back(nr, nc);\n                    }\n                }\n                q = move(new_q);\n            }\n            return dist;\n        };\n\n        auto dist = bfs();\n        vector&lt;vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt;&gt; buckets((size(grid) - 1) + (size(grid[0]) - 1) + 1);\n        for (int r = 0; r &lt; size(grid); ++r) {\n            for (int c = 0; c &lt; size(grid[0]); ++c) {\n                buckets[dist[r][c]].emplace_back(r, c);\n            }\n        }\n        vector&lt;vector&lt;bool&gt;&gt; lookup(size(grid), vector&lt;bool&gt;(size(grid[0])));\n        UnionFind uf(size(grid) * size(grid[0]));\n        int d = size(buckets) - 1;\n        for (; d &gt;= 0; --d) {\n            for (const auto&amp; [r, c] : buckets[d]) {\n                for (const auto&amp; [dr, dc] : DIRECTIONS) {\n                    const int nr = r + dr, nc = c + dc;\n                    if (!(0 &lt;= nr &amp;&amp; nr &lt; size(dist) &amp;&amp; 0 &lt;= nc &amp;&amp; nc &lt; size(dist[0]) &amp;&amp; lookup[nr][nc])) {\n                        continue;\n                    }\n                    uf.union_set(nr * size(grid[0]) + nc, r * size(grid[0]) + c);\n                }\n                lookup[r][c] = true;\n            }\n            if (uf.find_set(0 * size(grid[0]) + 0) == uf.find_set((size(grid) - 1) * size(grid[0]) + (size(grid[0]) - 1))) {\n                break;\n            }\n        }\n        return d;\n    }\n\nprivate:\nclass UnionFind {\n    public:\n        UnionFind(int n)\n         : set_(n)\n         , rank_(n) {\n            iota(begin(set_), end(set_), 0);\n        }\n\n        int find_set(int x) {\n           if (set_[x] != x) {\n               set_[x] = find_set(set_[x]);  // Path compression.\n           }\n           return set_[x];\n        }\n\n        bool union_set(int x, int y) {\n            x = find_set(x), y = find_set(y);\n            if (x == y) {\n                return false;\n            }\n            if (rank_[x] &gt; rank_[y]) {\n                swap(x, y);\n            }\n            set_[x] = y;  // Union by rank.\n            if (rank_[x] == rank_[y]) {\n                ++rank_[y];\n            }\n            return true;\n        }\n\n    private:\n        vector&lt;int&gt; set_;\n        vector&lt;int&gt; rank_;\n    };\n};\n\n// Time:  O(n^2 * logn)\n// Space: O(n^2)\n// bfs, dijkstra&#x27;s algorithm\nclass Solution2 {\npublic:\n    int maximumSafenessFactor(vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt;&amp; grid) {\n        static const vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; DIRECTIONS = {{1, 0}, {0, 1}, {-1, 0}, {0, -1}};\n        const auto&amp; bfs = [&amp;]() {\n            vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt; dist(size(grid), vector&lt;int&gt;(size(grid[0]), -1));\n            vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; q;\n            for (int r = 0; r &lt; size(grid); ++r) {\n                for (int c = 0; c &lt; size(grid[0]); ++c) {\n                    if (grid[r][c]) {\n                        dist[r][c] = 0;\n                        q.emplace_back(r, c);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            int d = 0;\n            for (int d = 0; !empty(q); ++d) {\n                vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; new_q;\n                for (const auto&amp; [r, c] : q) {\n                    for (const auto&amp; [dr, dc] : DIRECTIONS) {\n                        const int nr = r + dr, nc = c + dc;\n                        if (!(0 &lt;= nr &amp;&amp; nr &lt; size(dist) &amp;&amp; 0 &lt;= nc &amp;&amp; nc &lt; size(dist[0]) &amp;&amp; dist[nr][nc] == -1)) {\n                            continue;\n                        }\n                        dist[nr][nc] = d + 1;\n                        new_q.emplace_back(nr, nc);\n                    }\n                }\n                q = move(new_q);\n            }\n            return dist;\n        };\n\n        auto dist = bfs();\n        const auto&amp; dijkstra = [&amp;](const auto&amp; start, const auto&amp; target) {\n            priority_queue&lt;pair&lt;int, pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt;&gt; max_heap;\n            max_heap.emplace(dist[start.first][start.second], start);\n            dist[start.first][start.second] = -1;\n            while (!empty(max_heap)) {\n                auto [curr, u] = max_heap.top(); max_heap.pop();\n                if (u == target) {\n                    return curr;\n                }\n                for (const auto&amp; [dr, dc] : DIRECTIONS) {\n                    const int nr = u.first + dr, nc = u.second + dc;\n                    if (!(0 &lt;= nr &amp;&amp; nr &lt; size(dist) &amp;&amp; 0 &lt;= nc &amp;&amp; nc &lt; size(dist[0]) &amp;&amp; dist[nr][nc] != -1)) {\n                        continue;\n                    }\n                    max_heap.emplace(min(curr, dist[nr][nc]), pair(nr, nc));\n                    dist[nr][nc] = -1;\n                }\n            }\n            return -1;\n        };\n\n        return dijkstra(pair(0, 0), pair(static_cast&lt;int&gt;(size(dist) - 1), static_cast&lt;int&gt;(size(dist[0]) - 1)));\n    }\n};\n\n// Time:  O(n^2 * logn)\n// Space: O(n^2)\n// bfs, binary search\nclass Solution3 {\npublic:\n    int maximumSafenessFactor(vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt;&amp; grid) {\n        static const vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; DIRECTIONS = {{1, 0}, {0, 1}, {-1, 0}, {0, -1}};\n        const auto&amp; bfs = [&amp;]() {\n            vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt; dist(size(grid), vector&lt;int&gt;(size(grid[0]), -1));\n            vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; q;\n            for (int r = 0; r &lt; size(grid); ++r) {\n                for (int c = 0; c &lt; size(grid[0]); ++c) {\n                    if (grid[r][c]) {\n                        dist[r][c] = 0;\n                        q.emplace_back(r, c);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            int d = 0;\n            for (int d = 0; !empty(q); ++d) {\n                vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; new_q;\n                for (const auto&amp; [r, c] : q) {\n                    for (const auto&amp; [dr, dc] : DIRECTIONS) {\n                        const int nr = r + dr, nc = c + dc;\n                        if (!(0 &lt;= nr &amp;&amp; nr &lt; size(dist) &amp;&amp; 0 &lt;= nc &amp;&amp; nc &lt; size(dist[0]) &amp;&amp; dist[nr][nc] == -1)) {\n                            continue;\n                        }\n                        dist[nr][nc] = d + 1;\n                        new_q.emplace_back(nr, nc);\n                    }\n                }\n                q = move(new_q);\n            }\n            return dist;\n        };\n\n        const auto&amp; dist = bfs();\n        const auto&amp; check = [&amp;](int x) {\n            vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt; lookup(size(dist), vector&lt;int&gt;(size(dist[0])));\n            vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; q = {{0, 0}};\n            lookup[0][0] = 1;\n            while (!empty(q)) {\n                vector&lt;pair&lt;int, int&gt;&gt; new_q;\n                for (const auto&amp; [r, c] : q) {\n                    for (const auto&amp; [dr, dc] : DIRECTIONS) {\n                        const int nr = r + dr, nc = c + dc;\n                        if (!(0 &lt;= nr &amp;&amp; nr &lt; size(dist) &amp;&amp; 0 &lt;= nc &amp;&amp; nc &lt; size(dist[0]) &amp;&amp; dist[nr][nc] &gt;= x &amp;&amp; !lookup[nr][nc])) {\n                            continue;\n                        }\n                        lookup[nr][nc] = 1;\n                        new_q.emplace_back(nr, nc);\n                    }\n                }\n                q = move(new_q);\n            }\n            return lookup.back().back();\n        };\n\n        int left = 0, right = dist[0][0];\n        while (left &lt;= right) {\n            const auto&amp; mid = left + (right - left) / 2;\n            if (!check(mid)) {\n                right = mid - 1;\n            } else {\n                left = mid + 1;\n            }\n        }\n        return right;\n    }\n};\n</code></pre></div></div></div><!--$--><!--/$--></main><footer class=\"mt-20 border-t border-border bg-sidebar\"><div class=\"container-af py-12 grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4\"><div><p class=\"font-bold text-lg\">AlgoForge</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground max-w-xs\">Master coding interviews with patterns, roadmaps, and solutions</p></div><div><p class=\"font-semibold text-sm mb-3\">Learn</p><ul class=\"space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground\"><li><a class=\"hover:text-primary\" href=\"/problems\">Problems</a></li><li><a class=\"hover:text-primary\" href=\"/patterns\">Patterns</a></li><li><a class=\"hover:text-primary\" href=\"/roadmaps\">Roadmaps</a></li><li><a class=\"hover:text-primary\" href=\"/blind-75\">Blind 75</a></li><li><a class=\"hover:text-primary\" href=\"/grind-169\">Grind 169</a></li></ul></div><div><p class=\"font-semibold text-sm mb-3\">Interview</p><ul class=\"space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground\"><li><a cl